ocalhost\r\n```\r\n\r\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In my test, In Robocup3dsPlugin.cc , by using the following commands joints velocity can not be controlled to be Zero.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">model</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">GetJoint</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">kv</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">first</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">SetVelocity</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>In order to test, after running the simulator, a Robocup team binary can be downloaded from this <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://chaosscripting.net/files/competitions/RoboCup/WorldCup/2015/3DSim/binaries/utaustinvilla.tar.bz2\" rel=\"nofollow\">link</a>, and run the whole team using the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-linux\"><pre><span></span>./start.sh localhost\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2015-08-06T18:58:56.709682+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2015-11-05T01:14:28.472454+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 7}